{"body": "I'm not a fan.  Agile Development with Rails, I suggest adding \"as: 'store'\".  As the root helper takes only one parameter, so you will need to add 'to:'.  This is not obvious.\r\n    \r\nPerhaps the root helper could be modified to accept two parameters, and if the first is a string and the second is a hash will construct the proper hash?  Example:\r\n\r\n    root 'store#index', as: 'store'", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14114394", "created_at": "2013-02-26T13:45:35Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9419#issuecomment-14114394", "updated_at": "2013-02-26T13:45:35Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9419, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/rubys", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/e2dda5e47fccc5ff0daa87debf48162b?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fed519c02f134f2cdd836cba387b6a3c8.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/received_events", "gravatar_id": "e2dda5e47fccc5ff0daa87debf48162b", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "rubys", "type": "User", "id": 4815, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/rubys/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237ea2abd3543c15100994e"}, "id": 14114394, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/9419"}
